# LLM Fine-Tuning Pipeline

A production-ready pipeline for fine-tuning large language models (LLaMA 2, Mistral 7B) on domain-specific data using **QLoRA** (Quantized Low-Rank Adaptation) and **PEFT**. Tracks experiments with MLflow and serves the fine-tuned model via Hugging Face Inference Endpoints or a FastAPI wrapper.

Built for healthcare NLP use cases: clinical NER, ICD-10 coding, discharge summary generation — but fully adaptable to any domain.

---

## Why QLoRA?

Full fine-tuning a 7B model requires 80GB+ VRAM. QLoRA fine-tunes only a small set of adapter weights on a 4-bit quantized base model, enabling:
- Fine-tuning LLaMA 2 7B on a single A100 40GB (or 2x RTX 3090)
- 70-80% lower memory footprint vs. full fine-tuning
- Near-full-fine-tuning quality on domain tasks

---

## Architecture

```
Raw Domain Data (CSV / JSONL)
        │
        ▼
  Data Preprocessing
  (cleaning, dedup, format)
        │
        ▼
  Dataset Builder
  (instruction tuning format)
        │
        ▼
  QLoRA Fine-Tuning
  (PEFT + bitsandbytes + Transformers)
        │
        ▼
  MLflow Experiment Tracking
  (metrics, artifacts, model registry)
        │
        ▼
  Evaluation
  (ROUGE, F1, BLEU, perplexity)
        │
        ▼
  Model Export & Deployment
  (merge adapter → HF Hub / FastAPI)
```

---

## Tech Stack

| Component | Technology |
|---|---|
| Base Models | LLaMA 2 7B/13B, Mistral 7B Instruct |
| Fine-Tuning | PEFT (LoRA/QLoRA), bitsandbytes (4-bit NF4) |
| Training Framework | Hugging Face Transformers + TRL (SFTTrainer) |
| Experiment Tracking | MLflow |
| Evaluation | ROUGE, F1, BLEU, BERTScore |
| Model Serving | FastAPI + Hugging Face Inference Endpoints |
| GPU Optimization | Flash Attention 2, gradient checkpointing, paged AdamW |
| Containerization | Docker |

